metadata.name: Veil Of Entropy
metadata.description:
The veil is slipping off my tired face,  
although i heard the grass was greener  
on the other side, opposite of what i'd known  
i found myself walking a rough terrain to be content. 

the illusion of not be able was one i pierced at the age of 13, and i can't afford to look back. the reality i've set can not be facade, simply because of the fact, i am proof of existence.
